<t>
<field>HEDGE.TYPE.ID</field>
<desc>
            <p>The Amount Types which should be identified as a 'Hedged' type while building IAS.HEDGE.GROUP.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>APPLICATION</field>
<desc>
            <p>This field holds the applications for which the HEDGE.METHOD is defined.</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>Should be a valid application id.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>DESCRIPTION</field>
<desc>
            <p>Description of the Hedge Type.</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>35 digit alphanumeric Input.</p>
            <p>Mandatory Input</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>HEDGE.AMT.TYPE</field>
<desc>
            <p>This field contains a amount type that is used in building IAS.HEDGE.GROUP</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>Should be a valid IAS.AMOUNT.TYPE.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>HEDGE.METHOD</field>
<desc>
            <p>This provides the link to the Hedge Method table used for defining the calculation posting to be applied.</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>Valid IAS.HEDGE.METHOD.</p>
        </desc>
